body:
Can you attach an example that shows the issue?  (Must be openly licensed, ideally in test_regress format.)

```
`timescale 1ns / 1ps

interface generic_interface(
                            input clk,
                            input rst
                           );
    logic        valid;
    logic        ready;
    logic [31:0] data;

endinterface

class genericClass #(
                     int NUM_INTF = 5
                    );

    virtual generic_interface vif [NUM_INTF];

endclass

module tb_top();

    localparam int NUM_INTF = 6;

    genericClass #(NUM_INTF) genCls;

    logic tb_clk, tb_rst;

    generic_interface gen_if[NUM_INTF] (tb_clk, tb_rst);

    initial begin
        tb_clk = '0;
        tb_rst = '0;

        genCls = new();

        genCls.vif = gen_if;

        $finish();
    end

endmodule
```

```
The internal error shows the following: 

%Error: Internal Error: tb_top.sv:37:22: ../V3Broken.cpp:168: Broken link in node (or something without maybePointedTo): 'm_varp && !m_varp->brokeExists()' @ ./V3Ast__gen_impl.h:4694
                                       : ... note: In instance 'tb_top'
-node: VARREF 0x192ae00 <e1694> {d37aw} @dt=0x194d9d0@(w0)uc[0:5]  gen_if__Viftop [RV] <- VAR 0x19565d0 <e1833#> {d29ax} @dt=0x194d9d0@(w0)uc[0:5]  gen_if__Viftop [VSTATIC]  IFACEREF
   37 |         genCls.vif = gen_if;
      |                      ^~~~~~
- V3Ast.cpp:1323:     Dumping obj_dir/Vtb_top_990_final.tree
- V3StatsReport.cpp:231:statsReport:
```

Please note that when working with a single interface rather than an array of interfaces the code compiles.

What 'verilator' command line do we use to run your example?

`verilator --top-module tb_top --debug --binary --assert -Wall -Wno-fatal --timescale 1ns/1ps --trace --trace-structs  ./tb_top.sv`

What 'verilator --version' are you using?  Did you try it with the git master version?

`Verilator 5.030 2024-10-27 rev v5.030-45-g2cb1a8de7`

Have not tried at latest master head.

What OS and distribution are you using?

Fedora

May we assist you in trying to fix this in Verilator yourself?

Yes.
